12/08/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Twelve military police officers left for Afghanistan on Monday (11 August) to replace the Croatian unit deployed there earlier in the year. The platoon will operate as part of the International Security and Assistance Force.
Also Monday, the foreign ministry announced that Croatia had dispatched a fire fighting plane to Montenegro to help tame a large fire engulfing a pine forest. Montenegrin Foreign Minister Dragisa Burzan thanked Zagreb for the help and for ongoing co-operation in border areas. (HINA, HRT - 11/08/03)
